article.headline: Manhattan 71, Princeton 66
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Antoine Pearson scored 22 points and fellow guard Rashad Green added 16 points and seven rebounds to lead Manhattan over host Princeton 71-66 on Sunday. Manhattan (6-4) trailed 33-30 at halftime but shot 64 percent from the field in the second half to defeat the Tigers, who fell to 2-8. Princeton center Zach Finley scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds, while forward Kyle Koncz had 14 points for the Tigers.
